Merge pull request #42 from numberoverzero/master

Use --allow-empty for performance, resolves #32
drop unused content arg from commit function

Use --allow-empty for performance gelstudios/gitfiti#32

* Improves the size of the generated file:

2365211 new-gitfiti.sh
2529001 original-gitfiti.sh

* Cutting the number of executed commands in half (no more echo)
* Vastly reduces the amount of gc git performs during push

Merge pull request #34 from homeworkprod/cleanup

Python 3 fixes, refactoring, cleanup, and a first test.
Adjusted calendar SVG retrieval to work on Python 3, too.
Extracted "constant" for fallback image name.
Slightly streamlined user interface.
Make `raw_input` available on Python 3 by aliasing it to `input`.

Fix `str_to_sprite` on Python 3.

I'm using a list comprehension as it is easier to grok than `list(map(list, lines))`.
Fixed import of `urlopen[2]` on Python 3.

Introduced package for tests and added a test case for `str_to_sprite`.

The string variant of the "one-up" image, however, does not match the number-based one, to the expectation for the test had to be adjusted (basically replacing 1s with 0s).
Finding the highest daily commit count once is sufficient.
Use one-liner.
Extracted function calls.
Turn the optional Git URL argument into a mandatory one.
Introduced a few variables.
Turn the optional base URL argument into a mandatory one.
Extracted "constant" for GitHub base URL.
Prefix function names with verbs to avoid confusion (or upcoming conflicts) with variables.
Selectively employ one-liner conditionals for brevity.
Extracted function to request user input.
Fixed name and acronym case.
Create empty dict via literal syntax instead of function call.
Renamed function argument to reveal its meaning and to not override the built-in `input` function.
Clarified variable name.
Use string literal delimiters consistently (triple double-quotes for docstrings, [triple] single quotes for everything else where feasible).
Import the `datetime` and `timedelta` classes from the `datetime` package without having to fully qualify their uses.
Open file via `with` statement so it gets closed automatically.
Formatted with PEP 8 in mind. Inserted additional blank lines for readability. Ordered imports alphabetically. Removed unnecessary parentheses.
Update README.md
